content:
This is a quick, spoiler-free review for those who don't have time to read the long ones. It's also my first review and sorry if I make any grammar errors because English is not my mother tongue.
Zero no Tsukaima is a funny, simple anime whose only purpose is to make you relax and laugh, without having to think too much about it.
The good:
- It's funny;
- I found the plot to be enjoyable, even though it's simple;
- The characters are nice and easy to get used to.
The bad:
- Not a very well-thought story, it seems like everything was created on the fly;
- Full of plot holes;
-The characters and their relationships with each others don't evolve throughout the series.
